## Impact of 200% Text Zoom
- Resizing text to 200% results in both overlapping elements and the need for horizontal scrolling on the webpage (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Gemini).

### Element Overlap
-   Text and elements overlap due to the 200% zoom (3 of 3 GPT, 1 of 3 Gemini).
    -   **Specific Examples**: The "Enable Google Translate" button overlaps with the search bar (1 of 3 Gemini), or the "Accessibility Information" button experiences overlap (1 of 3 GPT).
    -   **Readability**: Despite the overlap, the text and elements might remain readable (1 of 3 GPT).

### Scrolling Requirement
-   Horizontal or lateral scrolling becomes necessary to view or access all content (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Gemini).
    -   **Extent**: The amount of scrolling required may be minimal (1 of 3 GPT).
